England goalkeeping legend Peter Shilton has signed a new two-year  contract as manager of Second Division Plymouth Argyle, less than 24 hours  after their 3-1 defeat by Burnley in the promotion play-off semi-finals.
First Division Middlesbrough, who recruited former Manchester United and  England captain Bryan Robson as manager this week, have made an approach to  Barnsley for Oakwell manager Viv Anderson, wanted as Robson's assistant at  Ayresome Park.
